s for responding to political and environmental crises and for thinking about how to transform the ways we live.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aHuman beingsxPhilosophy. 0aHuman beingsxPolitical aspects. 0aPhilosophical anthropology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374350zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374350423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374350.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles